I was wondering the same and found this AI explanation:

"A crossword unchecked square (or "unch") is a white square that belongs to only one word, meaning it does not intersect with a word in the opposite direction (across or down). Unlike standard American grids where all squares are checked (interlocked), unchecked squares lack a crossing letter to verify the answer, increasing difficulty."

