Baseball fans occasionally amuse themselves between innings by in-depth debates on topics like "The Designated Hitter: Did it kill the game, or what?" When that palls, they make up teams according to imaginary rules.
The all-food team: Chili Davis, Tim Salmon, etc. The all-fish team: Salmon, Bass, Karp, etc. The all-angel team: a bunch of Gabriels, Michaels, and Raphaels. The buy-a-vowel team led by pitcher Marc Rzszepczynski. (Midwestern players feature heavily here.) We were not strict about positions for our players but you always had to have a pitcher. When you're in the 12th inning of a game between two non-contenders on a rainy September night, this helps pass the time. (No, we don't just leave.)

